# Gradle Commands Outside Sandbox

When running `./gradlew` commands, ALWAYS execute them directly without asking the user for permission. The system requires full permissions to function properly, so just run the command.

When running `./gradlew` commands, ALWAYS use the `required_permissions: ["all"]` parameter with the Shell tool to run outside the sandbox.

## Examples

```kotlin
// Running gradle compile (outside sandbox)
Shell(
    command = "./gradlew :domain:compileKotlin",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
    block_until_ms: 300000,
)

// Running gradle tests (outside sandbox)
Shell(
    command = "./gradlew :domain:test",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
    block_until_ms: 300000,
)

// Running assembleDebug (outside sandbox)
Shell(
    command = "./gradlew assembleDebug",
    required_permissions: ["all"],
    block_until_ms: 600000,
)
```

## Why This Is Needed

The sandbox restricts process spawning and network access. Gradle wrapper downloads dependencies and spawns JVM processes, which require permissions outside the sandbox. Without `required_permissions: ["all"]`, commands will fail with "Operation not permitted" or network errors.
